The paper deals with algorithms for merging Burrows-Wheeler transforms and Longest Common Prefix arrays, which are fundamental data structures in string processing and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents an improvement to a previously proposed algorithm, which suggests that it could be relevant to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category. Additionally, the paper involves some combinatorial and graph-theoretic arguments, which could make it relevant to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) category. The paper also mentions applications to information retrieval, which could make it relevant to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Finally, the paper involves some experimental results and comparisons with other algorithms, which could make it relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
